<body class="ApplePlainTextBody" style="word-wrap: break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; -webkit-line-break: after-white-space; ">This one looks fine to me. &nbsp;Any other comments?<br><br><br>On Jan 7, 2008, at 10:39 AM, George Bosilca wrote:<br><br><blockquote type="cite">Or something like this, a hand-made sketched logo.<br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"> george.<br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite">&lt;Open-MPI-Doc.jpg&gt;<br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite">On Sep 26, 2007, at 3:09 AM, jody wrote:<br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">Or perhaps a pencil drawing one of the nice lines of the Open MPI Logo!<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">(Just a sketch)<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">But i guess things like this (introducing to many different elements) go against<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">the graphic grain....<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">On 9/25/07, Richard Friedman &lt;rchrd@sun.com&gt; wrote:<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">It would be even nicer if we could get the image of a pencil in the middle of the circle, to indicate docs.<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">I know, nobody uses a pencil any more, but it does signify writing, as in many of the gnome png icons, like this one:<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">which is for gedit.<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">(Just a suggestion)<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">jody wrote:<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">Hi all<br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">Basically the logos are nice,<br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">but i think they should have<br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">a closer relationship to the<br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">Open MPI logo than simply rounded corners;<br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">for instance the same colors (blue to black gradient)<br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">or those nice curved lines.<br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">_______________________________________________<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">docs mailing list<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">docs@open-mpi.org<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">http://www.open-mpi.org/mailman/listinfo.cgi/docs<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">&lt;doc-logo.png&gt;_______________________________________________<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">docs mailing list<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">docs@open-mpi.org<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><blockquote type="cite">http://www.open-mpi.org/mailman/listinfo.cgi/docs<br></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote type="cite"><br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite">_______________________________________________<br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite">docs mailing list<br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite">docs@open-mpi.org<br></blockquote><blockquote type="cite">http://www.open-mpi.org/mailman/listinfo.cgi/docs<br></blockq